observations.recommendation:
• Create an Inventory Committee and see to it that a physical count of properties is conducted every year with the report to be submitted to the Auditor on or before January 31 of the following year pursuant to Section 156 of COA Circular No. 92-386 and Section 124 of the Manual on the NGAS, Volume I;
• Require the Office of the Municipal Treasurer and Office of the Municipal Accountant to maintain property cards and ledger cards for each PPE item and reconcile both records with the physical count; and
• Require the Municipal Accountant to effect the necessary adjustments for all valid variances noted.

a) Require accountable officers with unliquidated cash advances to immediately submit the approved liquidation documents. If the cash advances are no longer needed, require the officers to refund the whole amount or the unused portion, as the case may be. Failure of the AO to liquidate his cash advance within the prescribed period shall constitute a valid cause for the withholding of his salary as provided for under paragraphs 9.2 and 9.3 of COA Circular 97-002 and the institution of other sanctions provided for under COA Circular 2012-004;
b) Direct the Municipal Accountant to closely implement and monitor the granting, utilization and liquidation of cash advances, send final demand letters separately to each accountable officer to remind the AOs of their outstanding cash advances and their liquidation. Stop from granting additional cash advance to officers and employees with outstanding cash advance;
c) Direct the accounting personnel who is in charge of maintaining the subsidiary records of the account “Advances to Officers and Employees” to regularly notify the municipal accountant of any outstanding cash advance of accountable officers to preclude the latter from processing and obligating additional cash advance; and
d) Impose the sanction of withholding of salaries of incumbent officials and employees with long-outstanding cash advances as provided under COA Circular No. 97-002 dated February 10, 1997.

